Standard form for printing a delivery note.
The header on the first page of the form contains the following
- Reference data (delivery with date, reference doc. ERP with date,
In contrast to the first page, the header of subsequent form pages
contains only the delivery number with date and the page numbering.
Additional header and footer texts are outputted on each page (see also
The item table contains the following data on the delivery items:
- Product short description and product text
- Batch number in the case of batch-managed products
- Sales order number with item number
- Reference document number ERP with item number
- Dangerous goods data at item level
In the version of the form supplied to customers, the first entry from
the form interface table IS_DLV_NOTE-HD_TXT is selected as header text
and the second entry from that table as footer text.
The form can be changed in such a way that special texts from this table
are used as header or footer text. Table IS_DLV_NOTE-HD_TXT contains the
field DESCRIPTION, which can be used as selection criterion.
Go to the <I>Initialization</> tab page via the nodes <I>Global
Settings-> Global Definitions</>. Change the coding for the selection of
header and footer text by specifying your own selection criteria.

technical drawings (blueprints) can be obtained in the calling framework
